$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'U ka sebelisa hexadecimal ho fetolela lipakeng tsa decimal le boleng ba binary. Mohlala, ho fetolela 10011011001010 ho ba hexadecimal ho ka fella ka 0x4F. Sena se bolela hore boleng ba 4F bo emela nomoro ea binary 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Lipalong le saenseng ea khomphutha, hexadecimal (hape ke basesisi ba 16, kapa hex) ke mokhoa oa boemo ba lipalo o nang le radix, kapa base, ea 16. E sebelisa matšoao a ikhethileng a leshome le metso e tšeletseng, hangata matšoao a 0–9 ho emela boleng ba zero ho isa ho robong. le A, B, C, D, E, F (kapa ka tsela e nngwe a–f) ho emela boleng ba leshome ho isa ho leshome le metso e mehlano. Ka mohlala, palo ea hexadecimal 2AF3 e lekana, ka decimal, ho (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) kapa 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Nomoro e &#39;ngoe le e &#39;ngoe ea hexadecimal e emela lipalo tse &#39;ne tsa binary (likotoana) (tseo hape li bitsoang &quot;nibble&quot;), &#39;me tšebeliso ea mantlha ea hexadecimal notation ke pontšo e bonolo ea motho ea boleng ba binary coded ho khomphutha le lisebelisoa tsa elektroniki tsa dijithale. Mohlala, boleng ba li-byte bo ka tloha ho 0 ho isa ho 255 (decimal) empa bo ka emeloa habonolo joalo ka linomoro tse peli tsa hexadecimal moleng oa 00 ho isa ho FF. Hexadecimal e boetse e sebelisoa hangata ho emela liaterese tsa memori ea komporo.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ke khutsufatso ea Hexadecimal, e ipapisitseng le sebopeho sa base -16 mme e sebelisetsoa ho nolofatsa tsela eo litaelo ho likhomphutha li emeloa ka eona. Sistimi ena ea linomoro tsa matšoao a 16 e entsoe e le mokhoa oa ho thibela nomoro ea binary ea 8-bit, kahoo data e ka kengoa likhomphutha ntle le matla. E ka hatisoa le ho thaepa ho sebelisoa linomoro tse peli tse fapaneng tsa hex ka nomoro e &#39;ngoe le e &#39;ngoe ea hex e bonts&#39;ang nibble kapa mohlomong sebopeho sa 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sistimi ena ea linomoro e sebelisa matšoao a 16 a emeloang ho tloha ho 0-9 kapa AF. 0–9 e emela lipalo ho fihla ho robong athe AF e emetsoe ke linomoro 10–15. Ha ho bapisoa le mefuta e meng e meraro ea litsamaiso tsa linomoro, sistimi ea linomoro tsa hexadecimal e nkoa e le eona e sebetsang ka ho fetisisa.';
